02:48.168 --> 02:49.920
Elena?

02:50.087 --> 02:52.510
What? Are you...?

02:52.673 --> 02:55.597
Oh.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.482
Midnight Sun Hotel.
How can I help you?

03:06.645 --> 03:10.070
Yeah, hello. I'm trying
to get hold of DCI Morton.

03:10.232 --> 03:12.576
Do you know where he is?

03:12.734 --> 03:14.953
Um, he's out.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.996
If you see him,
could you tell him...

03:20.158 --> 03:21.910
tell him to call his office?

03:22.077 --> 03:23.624
<i>Of course. Of course I will.</i>

03:23.787 --> 03:25.209
<i>Thank you. Bye.</i>

03:47.060 --> 03:48.357
Shh, shh, shh.

04:02.784 --> 04:05.378
Would you like me to take
you to the medical center?

04:07.664 --> 04:09.507
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

04:11.543 --> 04:13.796
Have you called the police?

04:13.962 --> 04:17.057
Is that why you're here?

04:17.214 --> 04:19.593
No. I wanted
to make sure you were okay.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.478
Not okay. I-I know that.

04:21.636 --> 04:23.229
Well, I'm not okay,
Mrs. Sutter.

04:27.017 --> 04:30.396
I'm very far from okay.

04:33.190 --> 04:35.409
When someone behaves the way

04:35.567 --> 04:37.911
your husband did, though...
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.165
...consequences are inevitable.

05:08.058 --> 05:10.311
He's all right, isn't he?

05:16.942 --> 05:19.195
I don't know.

05:20.612 --> 05:22.910
I don't know.

05:37.379 --> 05:39.381
<i>So, tech department</i>

05:39.548 --> 05:41.801
have enhanced this GPR scan,

05:41.967 --> 05:45.722
and you won't believe
what Pettigrew found.

05:45.887 --> 05:48.515
Those squiggly lines are bones.

05:48.682 --> 05:52.607
<i>Animal remains and tusks.</i>

05:52.769 --> 05:55.488
An elephant's graveyard
of mammoth beasts.

05:55.647 --> 06:00.448
<i>A hoard of ivory underneath
the ice worth a bloody fortune.</i>

06:00.610 --> 06:03.910
So,

06:04.072 --> 06:06.700
call me when you surface.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.698
They're here.

07:28.156 --> 07:30.375
<i>Thank you for coming.</i>

07:30.533 --> 07:32.831
<i>Please have a seat.</i>

07:44.047 --> 07:46.300
I want to talk to you

07:46.466 --> 07:48.719
about something
that affects Liam very much.

07:48.885 --> 07:50.478
Liam?

07:52.681 --> 07:56.481
What I'm about to say is
sensitive, so I need your word

07:56.643 --> 07:59.317
that you won't talk
about this to anyone.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.777
Okay.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.485
It's been suggested
that there are some kind

08:05.652 --> 08:08.155
of environmental toxins
on this island,

08:08.321 --> 08:09.914
and it maybe possible

08:10.073 --> 08:12.371
that Liam has
been affected.

08:13.660 --> 08:16.539
Now we want
to see if there are

08:16.705 --> 08:19.629
any of these toxins
in Liam's brain, and in order

08:19.791 --> 08:22.465
to do that, we need to take

08:22.627 --> 08:25.096
a little fluid from his spine.

08:25.255 --> 08:29.055
No. I'm sorry. I don't think
he's ready for that, not now.

08:29.217 --> 08:32.938
As I understand it, it's not
a complicated procedure.

08:33.096 --> 08:35.474
It's over
in a couple of minutes.

08:35.640 --> 08:39.361
I know how difficult
this must be.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.270
How?

08:41.438 --> 08:44.988
How would you know
that, Governor?

08:47.360 --> 08:49.579
We need to understand

08:49.738 --> 08:53.117
what made Liam attack
Professor Stoddart,

08:53.283 --> 08:55.377
because it may still be
affecting him.

08:55.535 --> 08:58.004
He may not
be getting any better.

08:58.163 --> 09:01.167
If we found
that a chemical

09:01.332 --> 09:03.175
had altered Liam's behavior,

09:03.334 --> 09:05.428
then that would change
everything.

09:09.799 --> 09:11.972
It would mean that what happened

09:12.135 --> 09:14.388
wasn't Liam's fault.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.427
I am here to see Shirley.

09:46.586 --> 09:49.180
The medical center said
she was here.

09:49.339 --> 09:50.591
Why was she moved?

09:51.966 --> 09:54.810
We needed to perform some tests.

09:54.969 --> 09:56.596
This place

09:56.763 --> 09:58.436
is for animals.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.396
I'm sorry.

10:00.558 --> 10:03.687
I need to see her.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.467
There now.

10:34.425 --> 10:36.519
Postmortems are
usually performed

10:36.678 --> 10:39.022
on the victim of a crime,
not the perpetrator.

10:39.180 --> 10:42.400
These were exceptional
circumstances.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.561
I can tell you now

10:44.727 --> 10:47.230
there was no violence
in Shirley.

10:47.397 --> 10:49.820
None at all.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.610
What happens when
you are finished?

10:51.776 --> 10:54.279
She's released to her family.

10:54.445 --> 10:56.664
There is only her mother.

10:56.823 --> 10:59.121
Then I don't know.

11:02.328 --> 11:05.582
No one seems to.

11:45.330 --> 11:48.049
What were you whispering about?

11:48.208 --> 11:51.803
Whispering?

11:51.961 --> 11:53.713
You and Dan were

11:53.880 --> 11:55.974
earlier today.

11:58.718 --> 12:01.016
Yes, um...

12:03.223 --> 12:04.725
What was it?

12:04.891 --> 12:07.144
Dan thinks

12:07.310 --> 12:09.779
that we have
to be prepared for the worst.

12:11.147 --> 12:13.445
What?

12:20.740 --> 12:23.038
Is it your father's?

12:29.666 --> 12:31.634
Yeah.

12:37.757 --> 12:39.009
I'm so sorry.

12:41.052 --> 12:44.056
Carrie.

12:44.222 --> 12:45.144
Just get off of me!

12:49.394 --> 12:50.691
Don't say that!

12:50.853 --> 12:52.526
He's not dead! He's not!

12:52.689 --> 12:54.032
My dad wouldn't leave me.

12:54.190 --> 12:56.067
He's coming home.

13:02.824 --> 13:04.701
♪♪

13:12.625 --> 13:14.218
Carrie?

13:18.214 --> 13:20.262
Carrie?

13:20.425 --> 13:23.269
Open the door, please, Carrie.

13:27.515 --> 13:30.109
Liam, this is
going to hurt a bit, okay?

13:30.268 --> 13:32.862
It won't be for long.

13:42.488 --> 13:43.660
Shh, shh, shh.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.666
It's okay.
It's okay.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.202
Good boy.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.522
Good boy.

14:15.271 --> 14:16.989
Keep still.

14:24.072 --> 14:26.450
Thanks.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.711
That's it.

14:37.293 --> 14:39.011
How's it look?

14:41.130 --> 14:42.598
They're negative.

14:42.757 --> 14:45.636
Absolutely no trace of
PFAs in Liam's system.

14:48.763 --> 14:50.231
Shirley's levels were
through the roof.

14:50.390 --> 14:54.236
Yeah, well,
maybe it was her diet.

14:54.394 --> 14:56.692
Maybe how long
she's lived here.

14:56.854 --> 14:58.572
Maybe children process
PFAs differently.

14:58.731 --> 14:59.732
I don't know.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.152
I don't know enough.

15:04.070 --> 15:05.947
We hurt a little boy.

15:09.242 --> 15:11.540
Well, this is something

15:11.702 --> 15:12.794
we've eliminated.

15:12.954 --> 15:14.206
We move on.

15:14.372 --> 15:16.466
We rerun the
data with...

15:16.624 --> 15:17.796
with a different set
of search criteria.

15:17.959 --> 15:20.212
Yeah.

15:20.378 --> 15:22.301
I need some air.

15:27.885 --> 15:31.105
♪♪

15:58.958 --> 16:02.087
♪♪

16:33.534 --> 16:34.877
Daddy's home.

16:35.036 --> 16:37.255
Hanna, don't
drag your bag.

16:37.413 --> 16:39.131
Jason?

16:40.291 --> 16:42.419
Jase?

16:46.589 --> 16:47.465
Where's Daddy?

16:47.632 --> 16:49.509
Uh, he's, um...

16:49.675 --> 16:51.552
he's out.

16:54.013 --> 16:55.856
Go and get the rest
of your stuff

16:56.015 --> 16:57.892
out the car, luv.

16:59.060 --> 17:00.778
Jason!

17:09.111 --> 17:11.239
Baby!

17:11.405 --> 17:13.782
Wh-What happened?

17:26.837 --> 17:29.010
♪♪

17:43.938 --> 17:46.908
What do you think
you're doing?

17:47.066 --> 17:48.488
That sound he made.

17:48.651 --> 17:51.245
Mr. Sutter.

17:51.404 --> 17:53.657
Sounded like an animal
caught in a trap.

17:55.825 --> 17:58.453
I can't imagine being a dad

17:58.619 --> 18:02.294
and having to submit your
own child to pain like that.

18:02.456 --> 18:05.084
I'm just not...

18:05.251 --> 18:07.253
What?

18:07.420 --> 18:09.923
I came here to do research
for my PhD,

18:10.089 --> 18:15.346
not inject children
and witness a murder and...

18:27.106 --> 18:30.827
Liam Sutter had
an illness...

18:32.945 --> 18:35.664
...and was seen
by Dr. Allerdyce.

18:35.823 --> 18:39.669
Then Shirley
attacked her mum.

18:39.827 --> 18:41.795
So what if the
doctor is the link?

18:41.954 --> 18:44.298
There's a communicable
infection, a contagion,

18:44.457 --> 18:47.677
and the doctor is the agent.

18:49.837 --> 18:51.714
Vincent, we've
got their blood.

18:53.883 --> 18:55.351
Come and help me.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.015
Antibody profiles.

19:03.559 --> 19:06.984
Same antibodies,
same infection.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.023
I'll catch you up.

19:22.411 --> 19:25.255
Where did all this
happen, Jase?

19:25.414 --> 19:27.542
Please tell me.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.929
Were you in a fight?

19:33.255 --> 19:34.973
Were you drinking?

19:35.132 --> 19:37.009
Jason...

19:56.153 --> 19:58.121
I'm going to ring Ciaran.

19:58.280 --> 20:00.078
Okay?

20:19.885 --> 20:21.762
Once, I was you.

20:24.098 --> 20:27.068
Along time ago.

20:27.226 --> 20:30.526
You know, the worst part
of being in prison--

20:30.688 --> 20:32.611
it wasn't...

20:32.773 --> 20:34.650
it wasn't just being in prison.

20:38.237 --> 20:40.114
The worst part was...

20:42.283 --> 20:44.581
...waking up

20:44.744 --> 20:48.590
like if I still was stabbing.

20:51.208 --> 20:55.008
And it was like he was alive.

20:58.174 --> 20:59.767
And I couldn't control it.

20:59.925 --> 21:03.520
I would freeze

21:03.679 --> 21:06.353
and stay there for...

21:06.515 --> 21:08.358
hours.

21:11.520 --> 21:13.693
Because I would become aware of,

21:13.856 --> 21:17.577
you know,
all the things that I lost.

21:19.695 --> 21:23.165
My-my family, my friends, my...

21:24.909 --> 21:27.537
...myself.

21:27.703 --> 21:31.503
I wouldn't be the same anymore.

21:31.665 --> 21:34.088
Yeah.

21:34.251 --> 21:37.346
Just because of one moment.

21:37.505 --> 21:41.806
You know, just because of
a single moment.

22:02.279 --> 22:05.203
When my dad used to
come home from training,

22:05.366 --> 22:07.243
he would have loads of bruises.

22:07.409 --> 22:09.411
So my mum would give him

22:09.578 --> 22:11.171
some frozen peas.

22:21.465 --> 22:24.344
What were you
talking about just then?

22:26.470 --> 22:27.972
My memories.

22:49.243 --> 22:52.042
We've established that both
Liam's blood and Shirley's blood

22:52.204 --> 22:55.299
both contain the identical
type E immunoglobin isotypes.

22:55.457 --> 22:58.256
This means they had
a similar infection.

22:58.419 --> 22:59.887
What kind of infection?

23:02.756 --> 23:05.225
Type E is the body's
first line of defense

23:05.384 --> 23:07.102
against invasive
pathogens.

23:07.261 --> 23:11.232
Anything from tapeworms to...

23:11.390 --> 23:12.312
viruses.

23:12.474 --> 23:13.817
Are we looking
at a virus here?

23:13.976 --> 23:15.478
We don't know.

23:15.644 --> 23:17.112
But could a virus cause

23:17.271 --> 23:19.444
this psychotic behavior?

23:19.607 --> 23:21.860
I got thick skin.

23:24.028 --> 23:25.371
Goddamn it!

23:25.529 --> 23:26.746
Sorry.

23:26.906 --> 23:28.032
Have you been drinking?

23:28.198 --> 23:29.245
So, Natalie,

23:29.408 --> 23:32.833
how would
something like this spread?

23:32.995 --> 23:37.171
Blood, saliva,
a sneeze, a cough.

23:37.333 --> 23:38.926
So, by now,

23:39.084 --> 23:40.927
everyone in Fortitude
could be infected.

23:43.172 --> 23:44.765
We're talking about
the town doc.

23:46.383 --> 23:48.886
Mum, the door!

23:49.053 --> 23:51.431
Her daughter
sold everyone their food.

23:54.600 --> 23:56.102
I can't keep

23:56.268 --> 23:57.269
the island open.

23:57.436 --> 23:59.313
We have to contain any virus,

23:59.480 --> 24:01.198
infection,
whatever the hell this is.

24:01.357 --> 24:03.200
You're suggesting
we tell everyone

24:03.359 --> 24:06.238
there's a contagious disease
here but that they can't leave?

24:06.403 --> 24:10.033
800 armed civilians
and four police officers.

24:13.035 --> 24:15.879
All right, we announce
a rabies quarantine.

24:16.038 --> 24:17.585
The normal procedure.

24:17.748 --> 24:19.091
And we test everyone.

24:19.249 --> 24:22.002
You prepare the tests
for everyone in town.

24:22.169 --> 24:24.137
And medical staff
will carry them out,

24:24.296 --> 24:26.264
so nobody will panic.

24:27.424 --> 24:28.266
Oh, thank God.

24:28.425 --> 24:30.302
Where is he?

24:33.889 --> 24:36.733
Okay, darling?

24:36.892 --> 24:38.894
There's no doctor on
the island, Ciaran.

24:39.061 --> 24:40.358
What are we going to do?

24:48.570 --> 24:50.447
Jason?

24:52.074 --> 24:53.951
Jason!

24:58.288 --> 24:59.164
Jason!

25:17.433 --> 25:20.232
Let's go up into my
office, shall we?

25:20.394 --> 25:23.864
No. I want to know the results
of the test. Tell me.

25:26.900 --> 25:29.369
Nothing. They
found nothing.

25:30.863 --> 25:33.207
Which is... good news.

25:33.365 --> 25:35.288
I thought it was going
to be good news

25:35.451 --> 25:36.668
if they found
an environmental toxin

25:36.827 --> 25:38.124
inside him--
then he could be treated.

25:38.287 --> 25:39.664
I thought that
was good news.

25:39.830 --> 25:43.175
Well, it's good that
he hasn't been poisoned.

25:43.333 --> 25:45.176
So the chemicals...

25:45.335 --> 25:48.430
the toxins that they found
inside the bear,

25:48.589 --> 25:50.341
Jules... they didn't find
those inside my son?

25:50.507 --> 25:51.383
No.
So there's nothing

25:51.550 --> 25:53.427
to account
for what he did?

25:57.723 --> 25:59.441
Just himself.

26:00.559 --> 26:02.152
He did it.

26:04.229 --> 26:07.699
<i>So I have to
accept that the only thing</i>

26:07.858 --> 26:11.283
that's inside him
is some kind of evil.

26:16.992 --> 26:18.710
Oh, God.
Jules...

26:24.875 --> 26:26.752
♪♪

26:36.637 --> 26:38.514
♪♪

27:25.519 --> 27:27.317
♪♪

27:49.710 --> 27:51.553
When my stepfather

27:51.712 --> 27:54.056
was dying...

27:54.214 --> 27:57.343
I went into his room
and I...

27:57.509 --> 28:01.514
I asked him if there was
anything that he needed,

28:01.680 --> 28:04.149
and he said...

28:04.308 --> 28:07.608
"Eugene, the only thing
that matters now...

28:07.769 --> 28:11.023
is the quality of the light."

28:11.190 --> 28:13.659
I loved that.

28:13.817 --> 28:16.240
"The quality of the light."

28:19.656 --> 28:23.251
Dan didn't shoot
Pettigrew.

28:23.410 --> 28:24.787
I know that.

28:24.953 --> 28:26.250
You did.

28:27.664 --> 28:29.632
But Dan did this.

28:33.253 --> 28:34.846
Handcuffed him.

28:35.005 --> 28:36.678
He was being torn apart

28:36.840 --> 28:39.343
when you shot him.

28:39.509 --> 28:41.637
Tell me why.

28:43.347 --> 28:44.769
Tell me, Henry...

28:44.932 --> 28:47.606
or I have to take you
back to London.

29:00.614 --> 29:02.537
♪♪

29:06.411 --> 29:08.129
Fuck!

29:08.288 --> 29:09.961
Fuck!

29:10.123 --> 29:12.501
God, I came here
to die!

29:12.668 --> 29:15.592
This is totally unacceptable!

29:15.754 --> 29:17.381
What gives you
the fucking right?!

29:17.547 --> 29:19.049
Look what you

29:19.216 --> 29:20.934
made me do!

29:21.093 --> 29:23.596
Henry...

29:23.762 --> 29:25.639
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

29:28.350 --> 29:31.229
Now, come on, that's a good boy.

29:31.395 --> 29:32.738
Wh-What is it?
This'll help.

29:32.896 --> 29:33.943
It's morphine.
No!

29:34.106 --> 29:35.949
No morphine!
No! I don't want it!

29:36.108 --> 29:37.576
It must hurt
like hell.

29:37.734 --> 29:39.987
I am truly...

29:40.153 --> 29:42.747
truly sorry.

30:04.511 --> 30:07.014
Liam's test results
were negative.

31:01.151 --> 31:03.028
Are you okay?

31:09.326 --> 31:11.579
Why don't you have

31:11.745 --> 31:14.089
a shower,
go to bed.

31:14.247 --> 31:17.376
Got to look after yourself,
or you're no use to anyone.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.169
Don't say that.

31:19.336 --> 31:20.804
Say What?

31:20.962 --> 31:23.556
Don't say
I'm no use.

31:23.715 --> 31:25.012
Oh, Frank, I'm not saying that.

31:25.175 --> 31:26.392
I just mean you need...

31:26.551 --> 31:28.804
Listen to me, Jules.

31:28.970 --> 31:30.813
All war...

31:32.391 --> 31:35.065
...all military
training,

31:35.227 --> 31:39.152
everything I've done in my life
boils down to one thing.

31:40.315 --> 31:42.238
Protect.

31:42.401 --> 31:44.403
Defend the family.

31:48.448 --> 31:51.952
And that's at the very,
very heart of everything I am.

31:55.122 --> 31:56.840
Defend my family.

32:03.672 --> 32:05.549
Okay, Frank.

32:07.592 --> 32:09.515
Okay.

32:22.190 --> 32:24.158
♪♪

32:37.956 --> 32:41.085
Oh, okay, oh...

32:41.251 --> 32:43.345
What is it?
What is it,

32:43.503 --> 32:45.301
a nine-mi...
a nine-millimeter?

32:45.464 --> 32:46.386
Yeah.

32:46.548 --> 32:47.595
I can survive.

32:47.757 --> 32:48.758
That's survivable.

32:48.925 --> 32:50.097
Nine-millimeter.
Okay...

32:50.260 --> 32:51.557
okay... oh!

32:55.765 --> 32:57.938
It's just blood.

32:59.895 --> 33:01.397
Okay, I can survive.

33:01.563 --> 33:04.157
I don't want you
getting your hopes up,

33:04.316 --> 33:05.363
old son.

33:05.525 --> 33:06.993
Oh, God.

33:07.152 --> 33:09.575
;
Henry...

33:09.738 --> 33:12.412
give me the morphine.

33:12.574 --> 33:14.292
Here.
Give...

33:14.451 --> 33:15.748
give...
Here.

33:18.955 --> 33:20.252
Oh...

33:22.959 --> 33:25.883
Liver cancer.

33:26.046 --> 33:28.048
Fuck.

33:28.215 --> 33:32.061
Feels like I've been shot
in the fucking guts.

33:32.219 --> 33:34.438
Why? Why?

33:34.596 --> 33:36.644
I don't deserve this.

33:38.099 --> 33:39.942
I can't help that.

33:40.101 --> 33:42.524
I'm not your judge.

33:42.687 --> 33:45.190
This is just a thing
that happened.

33:47.442 --> 33:49.285
Like cancer.

33:51.613 --> 33:53.741
Fuck you.

33:53.907 --> 33:56.786
Oh, fuck you!

33:56.952 --> 33:58.625
Fuck...

33:58.787 --> 34:00.130
fuck you, old man!

34:00.288 --> 34:01.790
Fuck you!

34:01.957 --> 34:03.550
You have no right!
Goddamn it,

34:03.708 --> 34:05.130
you have
no fucking right!

34:05.293 --> 34:06.920
None!

34:07.087 --> 34:10.681
I came here to find
a fucking killer!

34:10.840 --> 34:13.434
To find justice...
that's all wrong.

34:13.592 --> 34:16.266
There's no justice
in this fucking place.

34:16.429 --> 34:17.851
There's no...

34:38.534 --> 34:41.129
I'm gonna make us some dinner.

34:41.288 --> 34:43.757
We sit together...

34:43.915 --> 34:45.757
at the table...

34:45.917 --> 34:47.510
eat dinner.

34:47.668 --> 34:50.969
You at the head
of the table. Yeah?

34:54.259 --> 34:55.601
Okay.

34:59.806 --> 35:02.434
What am I gonna make?

35:04.144 --> 35:07.068
What am I gonna cook
for you tonight?

35:09.566 --> 35:12.615
Would you pop out for me?

35:12.777 --> 35:15.530
I'll put the potatoes on if you get
some steaks from the supermarket.

35:15.697 --> 35:16.789
Steaks?

35:16.948 --> 35:20.248
Yeah, or pork chops,
whatever you fancy.

35:21.411 --> 35:23.288
Sure.

35:26.041 --> 35:27.714
Anything else?

35:31.129 --> 35:34.429
Ice cream.

35:34.591 --> 35:38.095
Pork chops and ice cream.

36:02.952 --> 36:04.169
Liam...

36:04.329 --> 36:07.208
you need to help me, okay?

36:07.374 --> 36:08.546
Up we go.

36:08.708 --> 36:10.585
G-Good boy.
Good boy.

36:40.323 --> 36:42.200
♪♪

36:58.007 --> 36:59.725
Oh, excuse me.
I want two tickets.

37:01.761 --> 37:02.887
Airport's closed.

37:03.054 --> 37:04.897
Rabies protocol.

37:05.056 --> 37:06.854
Governor called it
an hour ago.

37:07.016 --> 37:08.939
No one in or out
till the "all clear."

37:09.102 --> 37:10.945
That plane's about to take off.

37:11.104 --> 37:12.321
It's only the pilot on board.

37:12.480 --> 37:14.778
Well, he's taking us.
We're not a risk.

37:14.941 --> 37:17.319
Well, I'm afraid not,
Mrs. Sutter.

37:17.485 --> 37:19.328
Please stop.

37:19.487 --> 37:21.990
Take Liam home.
There is a rabies protocol.

37:25.243 --> 37:27.871
I have a weapon, Mrs. Sutter!

37:28.037 --> 37:29.710
Stop! I can't let him go,

37:29.873 --> 37:32.217
and you know why!

37:39.632 --> 37:41.885
Then shoot me! Go on!

37:42.051 --> 37:43.394
Go on!

38:02.280 --> 38:04.749
Please go back
to your homes!

38:22.091 --> 38:24.970
Skidoo's out of gas.

38:26.429 --> 38:29.649
It's a one-way ticket,
I'm afraid.

38:45.323 --> 38:47.621
Hen...

38:48.993 --> 38:50.791
You can save me.

38:50.954 --> 38:53.082
Hen... Hen...

38:53.248 --> 38:55.751
Call 'em.
Please?

38:55.917 --> 38:58.136
Call 'em now.

38:58.294 --> 39:00.547
Don't let me
die here.

39:00.713 --> 39:04.843
Hey.

39:06.845 --> 39:09.098
Nils Anderssen was
my great friend.

39:09.264 --> 39:11.517
Dan's father.

39:13.184 --> 39:17.815
The winter Dan was born,
I stayed with them.

39:17.981 --> 39:20.325
Nils and Carol.

39:20.483 --> 39:22.781
She was a...

39:27.574 --> 39:32.626
Nils always said that the moment
he first saw Carol,

39:32.787 --> 39:34.960
the universe cracked.

39:39.294 --> 39:42.468
I loved her, too.

39:42.630 --> 39:47.511
God, I longed for
and loved her so much.

39:51.639 --> 39:54.233
After young Dan
was born, I left.

39:54.392 --> 39:57.236
Traveled,
wandered the world.

39:57.395 --> 40:02.276
Nils became a cruel
and violent man.

40:03.401 --> 40:05.654
Husband and father.

40:05.820 --> 40:08.118
A monster, in fact.

40:14.704 --> 40:16.627
Huh.

40:16.789 --> 40:18.632
He's yours.

40:21.085 --> 40:23.304
Dan is yours.

40:27.383 --> 40:31.229
I left him with a monster,
abandoned them both.

40:34.182 --> 40:36.435
Tell him.

40:37.810 --> 40:41.405
T... Tell him.

41:03.211 --> 41:05.430
Mayday-

41:05.588 --> 41:07.431
Mayday. Mayday.

41:07.590 --> 41:09.558
This is a mayday call.

41:11.260 --> 41:13.513
Fortitude Police.
What's your situation?

41:14.847 --> 41:17.100
Henry, it's Dan.

41:17.266 --> 41:20.190
Where are you?
What's going on?

41:20.353 --> 41:22.572
What's your situation?

41:22.730 --> 41:26.030
I'm on the glacier, Dan.

41:26.192 --> 41:29.196
I'm with Detective Chief
Inspector Morton.

41:32.115 --> 41:34.959
I've shot him in the stomach,

41:35.118 --> 41:37.337
and he's going to die

41:37.495 --> 41:39.839
unless you come and get him.

41:48.756 --> 41:52.852
Why? Why the hell
did you shoot him, Henry?

41:58.057 --> 42:00.310
He knows everything.

42:00.476 --> 42:02.729
All the proof he needs.

42:10.820 --> 42:14.040
That's the situation, Sheriff.

42:30.423 --> 42:32.141
You need to step outside...

43:07.585 --> 43:09.883
♪♪

43:26.604 --> 43:28.857
Dan, you okay?

43:29.023 --> 43:31.572
Huh?

43:31.734 --> 43:34.203
You Okay?

43:34.362 --> 43:37.411
Yeah.

43:39.742 --> 43:41.995
Eric?

43:42.161 --> 43:44.459
Yeah.

43:46.499 --> 43:49.503
You'd make a good sheriff.

44:20.241 --> 44:22.539
